'''David Paymer''' (born [[August 30]], [[1950s#1954|1954]]) is an [[Wikipedia:Americans|American]] [[Wikipedia:Character actor|character actor]] and voice actor. In ''[[Star Wars]]'' media, he voiced [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker's]] boyhood friend [[Deacon|Deak]] in the [[Star Wars (radio)|''Star Wars'' radio drama]] in [[1981]], appearing in the first episode, "[[A Wind to Shake the Stars]]."

Outside of ''Star Wars'', Paymer has received acting nominations for [[Wikipedia:Golden Globe Awards|Golden Globe]],<ref name="Golden Globes">{{WebCite|url=https://goldenglobes.com/person/david-paymer/|title=David Paymer|work=[[Wikipedia:Golden Globe Awards|Golden Globes]]|archivedate=20190202041908}}</ref> [[Wikipedia:Actor Awards|Screen Actors Guild]],<ref name="SAG">{{WebCite|url=https://www.actorawards.org/awards/nominees-and-recipients/2nd-annual-screen-actors-guild-awards|title=The 2nd Annual Screen Actors Guild Awards Nominees & Recipients|work=[[Wikipedia:Actor Awards|Screen Actors Guild Awards]]|archivedate=20260109095927}}</ref> and [[Wikipedia:Academy Awards|Academy Awards]]. His alma mater, the [[Wikipedia:University of Michigan|University of Michigan]], has referred to him "Oh, THAT Guy!" and called him "arguably one of Hollywood’s greatest character actors."<ref name="University of Michigan">{{WebCite|url=https://smtd.umich.edu/oh-that-guy-david-paymer/|title=Oh, THAT Guy! – David Paymer|work=[[Wikipedia:University of Michigan|University of Michigan]] Music, Theatre and Dance|author=Marilou Carlin|date=2019-06-09|archivedate=20250714082541}}</ref>

